Phragmites karka

   [1676.jpg]
    Authority   (Retz.) Trin. ex Steud.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms   Phragmites communis Trin., Phragmites roxburghii
   Common names common reed
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 1676

   Notes
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial grass. (GMIN and GMAX estimated by the compiler).
   COMMON NAMES
   Pit-pit, Tropical reed.
   FURTHER INF
   Pit-pit can be found at elevations from near sea level to 2000 m in New
   Guinea. It only thrives in rainfall regimes as low as 200 mm when
   growing in swamps.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   SOURCES (R. karke (Retz.) Steud.)
   Skerman P 1990 pp 638-639 [DRA, RAIN, TEXT, PH, USE

